article.headline: Jaylon Johnson makes go-ahead layup as Tennessee Tech defeats VMI 72-71
article.description: — Rodney Johnson Jr. scored 13 points and Jaylon Johnson made a game-winning layup in the closing seconds as Tennessee Tech beat VMI 72-71 on Friday night.
article.linkText: Jaylon Johnson makes go-ahead layup as Tennessee Tech defeats VMI 72-71
article.story: WHITE SULPHUR SPRINGS, W.Va. -- — Rodney Johnson Jr. scored 13 points and Jaylon Johnson made a game-winning layup in the closing seconds as Tennessee Tech beat VMI 72-71 on Friday night. Jaylon Johnson also scored 13 points for the Golden Eagles (3-1). Daniel Egbuniwe shot 5 for 8, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. Augustinas Kiudulas led the Keydets (3-1) in scoring, finishing with 21 points, 12 rebounds, two steals and three blocks. TJ Johnson added 10 points and two steals for VMI. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
